      "evidence": [
        "Configuration shape is modeled twice: persisted config structs in `goseg/structs/configs.go` and patch/update structs in `goseg/config/config_update_schema.go`, requiring synchronized edits across files.",
        "Runtime dependency wiring is split into many callback bags and merge paths (`goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_core.go`, `goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_ops.go`), with many nil-guard delegation wrappers that add coordination complexity.",
        "Wi-Fi runtime includes parsing policy, process command orchestration, client lifecycle, device toggling, and captive sysctl behavior in one type (`goseg/system/wifi_runtime_methods.go`), and tests span many concern classes (`goseg/system/wifi_test.go`, `goseg/system/wifi_c2c_flow_test.go`).",
        "Contract conformance checks are duplicated across separate suites (`goseg/protocol/actions/actions_test.go` and `goseg/protocol/contracts/contracts_test.go`), increasing maintenance overhead for one logical contract policy."
      ],
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "confidence": "high"
